-- =============================================
-- TRACK 1: ENTREPRENEURSHIP & BUSINESS
-- =============================================

INSERT INTO training_modules (id, track_id, title, content, display_order, duration_mins, created_at)
VALUES
  (
    '44444444-0001-0001-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
    'The Entrepreneur Mindset',
    E'THE ENTREPRENEUR MINDSET\n\nBefore you build a business, you build a mindset. The way you think determines everything.\n\nWHAT IS AN ENTREPRENEUR?\nAn entrepreneur is someone who sees a problem and creates a solution — then figures out how to make money doing it. Entrepreneurs do not wait for someone to hand them an opportunity. They build their own.\n\nTHE EMPLOYEE vs. OWNER MINDSET:\nEmployee thinking: "What time do I get off?" "That''s not my job." "I do what I''m told."\nOwner thinking: "How do we make this better?" "I take responsibility for outcomes." "I create solutions."\n\nYou can practice owner thinking even before you own anything. It shows up in how you approach school, jobs, and relationships.\n\nKEY TRAITS OF ENTREPRENEURS:\n1. Problem Solvers — They look for needs, not just opportunities\n2. Risk Takers — They are comfortable with uncertainty\n3. Persistent — They fail, learn, and keep going\n4. Self-Starters — They do not wait to be told what to do\n5. Value Creators — They focus on what they can give, not just what they can get\n\nFAILURE IS PART OF THE PROCESS:\nEvery successful entrepreneur has a long list of failures. Michael Jordan was cut from his high school basketball team. Steve Jobs was fired from Apple — the company he founded. Failure is not the opposite of success. It is part of the path.\n\nSTART WHERE YOU ARE:\nYou do not need money, connections, or a perfect idea to start thinking like an entrepreneur. You need observation skills, a willingness to work, and the courage to begin.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- What problems do you notice in your school, neighborhood, or community?\n- What skills or talents do you have that other people value?\n- What would you build if you knew you could not fail?',
    1, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0001-0002-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
    'From Idea to Business',
    E'FROM IDEA TO BUSINESS\n\nEveryone has ideas. Few people do anything with them. This module is about closing that gap.\n\nTHE BUSINESS IDEA FORMULA:\nA good business idea = a problem you can solve + people willing to pay for the solution.\n\nThat''s it. Do not overcomplicate it.\n\nTYPES OF BUSINESSES A YOUNG PERSON CAN START TODAY:\n- Service businesses: lawn care, car washing, tutoring, tech help, cleaning\n- Creative businesses: photography, graphic design, music production, content creation\n- Resale businesses: flipping sneakers, thrift store finds, electronics\n- Digital businesses: online courses, social media management, printables\n- Food businesses: baked goods, meal prep, catering (check local laws)\n\nTHE LEAN START:\nYou do not need a business plan, LLC, or website to start. You need:\n1. A clear offer (what you do)\n2. A price (what you charge)\n3. A customer (one person willing to pay)\n\nStart with one customer. Serve them well. Get a referral. Repeat.\n\nTHE BUSINESS MODEL CANVAS (SIMPLIFIED):\n- Who are your customers?\n- What problem do you solve for them?\n- How do you reach them?\n- What does it cost you to deliver?\n- What do you charge?\n\nCOMPETITION IS GOOD:\nIf other people are already doing what you want to do, that means there is a market. Your job is not to eliminate the competition — it is to be better in one specific way.\n\nPROTECT YOUR IDEA BY STARTING:\nIdeas are worthless without execution. The only way to protect an idea is to build it before someone else does.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- What is one service or product you could offer starting this week?\n- Who in your life might be your first customer?\n- What would you charge, and why?',
    2, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0001-0003-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
    'Money, Pricing & Profit',
    E'MONEY, PRICING & PROFIT\n\nYou can be great at your craft and still go broke if you do not understand numbers. Let''s fix that.\n\nTHREE NUMBERS EVERY BUSINESS OWNER MUST KNOW:\n1. Revenue — The total money that comes in\n2. Expenses — The total money that goes out to run the business\n3. Profit — What is left over: Revenue - Expenses = Profit\n\nExample: You charge $50 to cut a lawn. You spend $10 on gas. Your profit is $40.\n\nHOW TO SET YOUR PRICE:\nMany beginners undercharge because they are afraid no one will pay. This is a trap. Here is a simple pricing formula:\n\nCost to deliver + your time (valued fairly) + 20-30% margin = your price\n\nNever price based purely on what competitors charge. Know your own costs first.\n\nTHE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN CASH AND PROFIT:\nJust because money is in your hand does not mean you made a profit. If you spent $200 buying supplies and only collected $150, you lost $50 even if it feels like you made money.\n\nPAY YOURSELF FIRST (IN BUSINESS TOO):\nWhen profit comes in, set aside:\n- 20% for taxes (you will owe this eventually)\n- 20% for business reinvestment (growth, supplies, marketing)\n- 60% for yourself\n\nCHARGE WHAT YOU ARE WORTH:\nLow prices attract customers who do not value your work. High prices (backed by quality) attract customers who respect you. Do not compete on price — compete on value.\n\nKEEP SIMPLE RECORDS:\nUse a notebook, spreadsheet, or free app (Wave, QuickBooks Simple Start) to track every dollar in and out. This habit separates serious entrepreneurs from hobbyists.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- What would you charge for your business idea? How did you arrive at that number?\n- What expenses would you have?\n- What is your projected profit per customer?',
    3, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0001-0004-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
    'Marketing & Building Your Brand',
    E'MARKETING & BUILDING YOUR BRAND\n\nYou can have the best product in the world, but if nobody knows about it, you have nothing. Marketing is how you tell your story.\n\nWHAT IS A BRAND?\nYour brand is not just your logo. It is the feeling people get when they think of you. It is the promise you make and keep every time you show up.\n\nYOUR PERSONAL BRAND STARTS NOW:\nEverything you post, say, and do in public is building your brand — even if you do not have a business yet. Employers, customers, and mentors Google you. Make sure what they find tells the right story.\n\nTHE THREE MARKETING QUESTIONS:\n1. Who is your customer? (Be specific — not "everyone")\n2. Where do they spend their time? (Online? In your neighborhood?)\n3. What message will make them choose you?\n\nFREE MARKETING STRATEGIES:\n- Word of mouth: Do great work and ask for referrals\n- Social media: Document your work on Instagram, TikTok, or YouTube\n- Flyers: Simple, targeted, and still effective in neighborhoods\n- Community: Join groups, show up, and let people know what you do\n\nSTORYTELLING SELLS:\nPeople buy from people they trust. Share your story — why you started, what you stand for, and what results you get for customers. Be authentic.\n\nFOLLOW UP:\n80% of sales happen after the 5th contact. Most people give up after the 1st. Follow up with potential customers consistently and respectfully.\n\nYOUR REPUTATION IS YOUR MARKETING:\nShow up on time. Do what you say. Go above and beyond. A satisfied customer tells 3 people. An unsatisfied customer tells 30.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- How would you describe your brand in three words?\n- What platform would you use to market your business and why?\n- What is one thing you could do this week to tell more people about what you offer?',
    4, 20, NOW()
  ),


-- =============================================
-- TRACK 2: LIFE SKILLS
-- =============================================

  (
    '44444444-0002-0001-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000002',
    'Managing Your Time & Space',
    E'MANAGING YOUR TIME & SPACE\n\nYour environment and your schedule are either working for you or against you. You get to decide which.\n\nWHY TIME MANAGEMENT MATTERS:\nTime is the one resource you can never get back. How you spend your hours determines what your life becomes. Successful people do not have more hours — they use them differently.\n\nTHE PRIORITY MATRIX:\nNot everything on your to-do list deserves equal attention. Sort tasks into four categories:\n1. Important + Urgent: Do it now (deadlines, emergencies)\n2. Important + Not Urgent: Schedule it (studying, exercise, planning)\n3. Not Important + Urgent: Delegate it if possible (some interruptions)\n4. Not Important + Not Urgent: Eliminate it (mindless scrolling, time wasters)\n\nMost people spend too much time in category 4 and not enough in category 2.\n\nBUILD A DAILY ROUTINE:\nWin the morning, win the day. A consistent morning routine — even 30 minutes of intentional activity before checking your phone — sets a powerful tone.\n\nSuggested morning anchors:\n- Make your bed (starts with a win)\n- Move your body (even 10 minutes)\n- Review your goals or intentions for the day\n\nYOUR SPACE REFLECTS YOUR MIND:\nA clean, organized space supports clear thinking. Disorder around you creates disorder in your head. You do not need to be perfect — just intentional.\n\nBasic space management habits:\n- Make your bed every morning\n- Do not let dishes sit overnight\n- Everything has a home — return things after use\n- Do a 10-minute clean-up before bed\n\nSAY NO TO PROTECT YOUR TIME:\nYou cannot do everything. Saying no to things that do not align with your goals is not selfish — it is strategic.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- What is your current morning routine? What would you change?\n- What do you waste the most time on?\n- What is one new habit you want to build this month?',
    1, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0002-0002-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000002',
    'Cooking & Nutrition Basics',
    E'COOKING & NUTRITION BASICS\n\nA man who can feed himself is a man who is never fully dependent. Cooking is not just a life skill — it is freedom.\n\nWHY LEARN TO COOK:\n- It saves money (eating out costs 3-5x more than cooking)\n- It gives you control over what goes into your body\n- It is a powerful life skill for independence\n- It impresses people. A man who can cook is an asset.\n\nTHE FIVE MEALS EVERY MAN SHOULD KNOW:\n1. Scrambled eggs + toast (breakfast)\n2. Rice and protein (lunch/dinner base)\n3. Pasta with sauce (quick dinner)\n4. Stir-fry vegetables and chicken (healthy weeknight meal)\n5. A simple salad (quick, no-cook lunch)\n\nKITCHEN SAFETY BASICS:\n- Wash your hands before handling food\n- Keep raw meat separate from other foods\n- Do not leave the stove unattended\n- Use a cutting board — protect the counter and your fingers\n- Know where the fire extinguisher is\n\nNUTRITION FUNDAMENTALS:\nYour body runs on fuel. The quality of your fuel determines your energy, focus, and performance.\n\n- Protein: Builds muscle and keeps you full (chicken, eggs, beans, fish)\n- Carbohydrates: Your body''s fuel source (rice, oats, bread, fruit)\n- Fats: Brain function, hormones, energy (nuts, avocado, olive oil)\n- Water: Everything depends on hydration. Drink at least 8 glasses a day.\n\nREAD LABELS:\nMost packaged foods are engineered to make you overeat. Learn to read the ingredients list — if you cannot pronounce most of it, put it back.\n\nMEAL PREP:\nCook once, eat multiple times. Preparing your meals on Sunday saves money and keeps you eating well throughout the week.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- What meals can you currently cook on your own?\n- What is one new meal you want to learn this week?\n- How does your current diet affect your energy and mood?',
    2, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0002-0003-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000002',
    'Laundry, Cleaning & Home Basics',
    E'LAUNDRY, CLEANING & HOME BASICS\n\nThese are not chores. These are the habits that define whether you live like a king or a child in a man''s body.\n\nLAUNDRY 101:\nDo not be the person who ruins their clothes or shows up looking unkempt because nobody taught them.\n\n- Sort clothes: Darks with darks, lights with lights, delicates separately\n- Check the tag: It tells you exactly how to wash the item\n- Water temperature: Cold for most clothes (prevents shrinking), warm for towels/sheets\n- Never overfill the machine: Clothes need room to get clean\n- Do not leave wet clothes in the machine: They will smell\n- Fold or hang immediately: Prevents wrinkles\n\nIRONING BASICS:\n- Different fabrics need different heat settings (check the tag)\n- Always iron on the inside if you are unsure\n- A steamer is easier and often good enough\n\nCLEANING YOUR SPACE:\nYou should be able to clean your bedroom, bathroom, and kitchen. These are non-negotiable.\n\nWeekly cleaning basics:\n- Vacuum or sweep floors\n- Wipe down surfaces (counters, sink, toilet)\n- Take out trash before it overflows\n- Clean dishes or load the dishwasher daily\n\nSHOPPING FOR BASICS:\nLearn to buy cleaning supplies, toiletries, and household staples. Keep a running list. Do not wait until you are out of something to buy it.\n\nBASIC REPAIRS:\nEvery man should know how to:\n- Unclog a drain\n- Replace a light bulb\n- Tighten a screw\n- Patch a small hole in the wall\n- Turn off the water supply in an emergency\n\nYOUR SPACE IS A REFLECTION:\nHow you maintain your environment tells people — and yourself — what kind of person you are.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- On a scale of 1-10, how clean and organized is your space right now?\n- What is one area of your living space you could improve this week?\n- What household task have you been avoiding that you should learn?',
    3, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0002-0004-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000002',
    'Transportation, Appointments & Adulting',
    E'TRANSPORTATION, APPOINTMENTS & ADULTING\n\nNavigating the real world requires practical skills that most young men learn the hard way. Learn them here instead.\n\nGETTING AROUND:\nKnow your transportation options and plan ahead:\n- Public transit: Know the routes, fares, and schedules in your city\n- Rideshare: Uber/Lyft are convenient but expensive long-term. Budget for it.\n- Driver''s license: A major milestone — know the requirements in your state\n- Car basics: Oil changes, tire pressure, how to change a flat, what warning lights mean\n\nMANAGING APPOINTMENTS:\nMissing appointments is unprofessional and often costly. Build these habits:\n- Add every appointment to your phone calendar immediately\n- Set a reminder 24 hours and 1 hour before\n- Arrive 5-10 minutes early (on time is late)\n- If you must cancel, give as much notice as possible and reschedule immediately\n\nIMPORTANT DOCUMENTS EVERY ADULT NEEDS:\nKeep these in a safe place and know where they are:\n- Birth certificate\n- Social Security card\n- State ID or driver''s license\n- Insurance cards\n- Any school or legal records\n\nBASIC HEALTHCARE:\n- Know your primary care doctor and dentist\n- Schedule annual check-ups even when you feel fine\n- Know your health insurance basics: deductible, co-pay, in-network\n- Know basic first aid: how to clean and bandage a wound, what to do in an emergency\n\nFILING TAXES:\nOnce you earn income, you will likely need to file taxes. Key points:\n- W-2 from employers, 1099 for self-employment\n- Deadline is typically April 15\n- Free options: IRS Free File, VITA sites, TurboTax Free\n- Keep receipts for any business-related expenses\n\nREFLECTION:\n- Do you know where all your important documents are?\n- When was your last doctor or dentist visit?\n- What is one "adulting" task you have been putting off?',
    4, 20, NOW()
  ),


-- =============================================
-- TRACK 3: HEALTH & WELLNESS
-- =============================================

  (
    '44444444-0003-0001-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000003',
    'Your Body Is Your Asset',
    E'YOUR BODY IS YOUR ASSET\n\nYou only get one body. How you treat it in your teens and twenties determines your quality of life for decades.\n\nWHY FITNESS MATTERS BEYOND LOOKING GOOD:\n- Mental clarity: Exercise literally makes you smarter and reduces anxiety\n- Energy: Fit people have more energy for everything else in life\n- Confidence: Physical strength builds mental toughness\n- Longevity: The habits you build now protect your health at 40, 60, and beyond\n- Discipline: Training your body trains your mind\n\nTHE BASICS OF PHYSICAL FITNESS:\nYou do not need a gym membership. You need consistency.\n\nThree pillars of fitness:\n1. Strength training: Builds muscle, increases metabolism, protects joints (pushups, pullups, squats, lifting)\n2. Cardiovascular exercise: Keeps your heart strong (running, jumping rope, cycling, sports)\n3. Flexibility and recovery: Prevents injury and keeps you moving well (stretching, yoga, foam rolling)\n\nA STARTER ROUTINE (NO GYM REQUIRED):\nMonday/Wednesday/Friday: 3 sets of pushups, squats, lunges, and planks\nTuesday/Thursday: 20-30 minutes of running or cardio\nWeekend: Active rest — play a sport, take a walk, stretch\n\nSLEEP IS TRAINING:\nYou do not grow during the workout. You grow during sleep. Most teenagers need 8-10 hours.\nPoor sleep = poor decision making, lower grades, more stress, slower recovery.\n\nHYDRATION:\nWater is the most underrated performance enhancer. Aim for at least 8 glasses (64 oz) per day — more if you are active.\nSigns you are dehydrated: headaches, low energy, poor concentration.\n\nAVOIDANCE:\n- Excessive alcohol damages every system in your body\n- Tobacco and vaping destroy lung capacity\n- Processed food and sugar spike energy then crash it\n\nREFLECTION:\n- How many days per week are you currently active?\n- What is your biggest barrier to exercise?\n- What is one physical goal you want to achieve in the next 90 days?',
    1, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0003-0002-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000003',
    'Mental Health & Emotional Strength',
    E'MENTAL HEALTH & EMOTIONAL STRENGTH\n\nStrong men feel things. The difference between strength and weakness is not whether you have emotions — it is what you do with them.\n\nTHE MENTAL HEALTH CRISIS IN YOUNG MEN:\nYoung men are experiencing record levels of anxiety, depression, and loneliness. Many suffer in silence because they were taught that asking for help is weak. That lie is costing lives.\n\nWHAT MENTAL HEALTH ACTUALLY IS:\nMental health is not about being happy all the time. It is about:\n- Being able to manage your emotions without being controlled by them\n- Maintaining relationships and functioning in daily life\n- Processing difficult experiences in healthy ways\n- Knowing when to ask for help\n\nCOMMON MENTAL HEALTH CHALLENGES:\n- Anxiety: Excessive worry, fear, or stress that interferes with life\n- Depression: Persistent sadness, low energy, loss of interest in things you once enjoyed\n- Anger issues: Explosions that hurt your relationships and your future\n- Trauma: Unprocessed pain from difficult experiences\n\nHEALTHY EMOTIONAL HABITS:\n1. Name what you feel — emotions cannot be managed until they are acknowledged\n2. Talk to someone — a mentor, counselor, trusted friend, or parent\n3. Move your body — exercise is one of the most effective treatments for mild depression and anxiety\n4. Limit social media — comparison is the thief of joy\n5. Journal — writing clarifies what you are actually feeling\n\nIT IS OKAY TO GET HELP:\nSeeing a therapist or counselor is not weakness. It is the same as going to the gym for your mind. The strongest men in the world have coaches and therapists.\n\nCRISIS RESOURCES:\n- 988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline: Call or text 988\n- Crisis Text Line: Text HOME to 741741\n\nREFLECTION:\n- How do you currently handle stress, anger, or sadness?\n- Is there something you have been carrying that you have not talked to anyone about?\n- Who in your life do you trust enough to be honest with?',
    2, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0003-0003-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000003',
    'Sleep, Stress & Recovery',
    E'SLEEP, STRESS & RECOVERY\n\nHighest performers in every field prioritize recovery. Most young men neglect it and wonder why they cannot perform.\n\nSLEEP: THE MOST UNDERRATED PERFORMANCE TOOL\n\nWhat happens when you sleep:\n- Your brain consolidates memories and learning\n- Your body repairs muscle tissue\n- Hormones that regulate growth, appetite, and mood are released\n- Your immune system strengthens\n\nSleep deprivation effects:\n- Reduced focus and decision-making ability\n- Increased emotional reactivity (more likely to lose your temper)\n- Weakened immune system\n- Weight gain (sleep affects hunger hormones)\n- Increased risk of anxiety and depression\n\nHOW TO SLEEP BETTER:\n- Set a consistent bedtime, even on weekends\n- No screens 30-60 minutes before bed (blue light suppresses melatonin)\n- Keep your room cool and dark\n- Avoid caffeine after 2pm\n- Do not eat heavy meals right before bed\n\nUNDERSTANDING STRESS:\nNot all stress is bad. Short-term stress can sharpen focus and motivate action. The problem is chronic, unmanaged stress.\n\nSigns of chronic stress:\n- Always feeling behind or overwhelmed\n- Headaches, stomach problems, or frequent illness\n- Difficulty concentrating\n- Irritability or emotional outbursts\n\nSTRESS MANAGEMENT TOOLS:\n1. Deep breathing — 4 counts in, hold 4, out 4. Activates the calm-down system.\n2. Exercise — burns off stress hormones physically\n3. Talking — processing stress with a trusted person reduces its power\n4. Boundaries — saying no to things that drain you\n5. Prayer and meditation — quieting the mind has documented health benefits\n\nRECOVERY IS NOT LAZINESS:\nResting, sleeping, and taking breaks are not signs of weakness. They are how you sustain high performance over time.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- How many hours of sleep do you typically get?\n- What is your biggest source of stress right now?\n- What is one recovery habit you want to add this week?',
    3, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0003-0004-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000003',
    'Avoiding Risky Behaviors',
    E'AVOIDING RISKY BEHAVIORS\n\nThe choices you make right now have a longer shelf life than you think. One decision can alter the next ten years.\n\nWHY THIS MATTERS NOW:\nThe teenage brain is still developing — specifically the prefrontal cortex, which controls impulse regulation and long-term thinking. This means you are wired to seek thrills and underestimate consequences. Knowing that gives you power over it.\n\nDRUGS AND ALCOHOL:\n- The adolescent brain is uniquely vulnerable to addiction. Starting early dramatically increases lifetime risk.\n- Marijuana affects memory, motivation, and brain development in teens — the science is clear.\n- Alcohol impairs judgment at exactly the moments when good judgment matters most.\n- No amount of peer pressure is worth a record, a hospital stay, or a funeral.\n\nSEXUAL HEALTH:\n- You are not ready for all the consequences of sex just because your body can do it.\n- STIs are common and often have no visible symptoms — protection is non-negotiable if you are active.\n- Unintended pregnancy changes two lives permanently. Take that seriously.\n- Pornography creates distorted expectations about sex and relationships that damage real intimacy.\n\nGANGS AND STREET VIOLENCE:\n- The streets will take more than they give. Every time.\n- The same loyalty code that draws people in is used to keep them trapped.\n- You cannot control where you were born, but you control where you are going.\n\nSOCIAL MEDIA AND REPUTATION:\n- Screenshots are forever. Criminal records are searchable.\n- What you do online is admissible in court, seen by colleges, and seen by employers.\n\nTHE EXIT PLAN:\nIf you are already in a situation that is pulling you down, there is always a way out. Talk to your mentor, a counselor, or a trusted adult. You do not have to solve it alone.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- What is the biggest risk in your current environment?\n- Who in your circle influences you toward positive or negative choices?\n- What is one boundary you want to set for yourself going forward?',
    4, 20, NOW()
  ),


-- =============================================
-- TRACK 4: FINANCIAL LITERACY
-- =============================================

  (
    '44444444-0004-0001-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000004',
    'Understanding Money',
    E'UNDERSTANDING MONEY\n\nMoney is not good or evil. It is a tool. The question is whether you will control it or it will control you.\n\nWHERE MONEY COMES FROM:\nMoney is exchanged for value. When you provide value — through a job, a skill, a product, or an investment — you receive money in return. The more value you create, the more money you can earn.\n\nTHE MONEY MINDSET:\nScarcity mindset: "There is never enough. I have to protect every dollar."\nAbundance mindset: "Money is a resource. I can earn more by creating more value."\n\nNeither extreme is healthy. You need to respect money without being controlled by fear of losing it.\n\nINCOME TYPES:\nActive income: You trade time for money (job, freelance work)\nPassive income: Money works for you (investments, rental income, royalties)\n\nThe goal over time is to build more passive income so your money generates money.\n\nNEEDS vs. WANTS:\nNeeds: Housing, food, transportation, basic clothing, healthcare\nWants: Subscriptions, new shoes, eating out, entertainment\n\nMost financial problems come from spending want-money before need-money is covered.\n\nTHE WEALTH EQUATION:\nIncome - Expenses = Savings/Investment\n\nYou can increase this by: earning more OR spending less. The fastest path is doing both simultaneously.\n\nWEALTH IS BUILT SLOWLY:\nAnyone promising quick riches is lying. Wealth is built through consistent earning, disciplined saving, and smart investing over years and decades.\n\nSTART NOW:\nEven $10 per week saved starting at age 16 becomes meaningful money by age 25 with compound interest. The most powerful factor in wealth-building is time. Start early.\n\nREFLECTION:\n- What is your current relationship with money? Is it healthy?\n- What is the difference between your income and expenses right now?\n- What would you do with $1,000 in savings?',
    1, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0004-0002-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000004',
    'Banking, Budgeting & Saving',
    E'BANKING, BUDGETING & SAVING\n\nThe man who manages small money well is trusted with larger amounts. Start building that track record now.\n\nBANKING BASICS:\nOpen a checking account as soon as you have income. Look for:\n- No monthly fees (or fees waived with direct deposit)\n- A debit card for everyday purchases\n- Online and mobile access\n- A companion savings account\n\nAvoid predatory options like check-cashing stores and payday lenders. They charge enormous fees to people who can least afford it.\n\nTHE BUDGET: YOUR MONEY PLAN\nA budget is not a restriction. It is a plan for where your money goes before it disappears.\n\nTHE 50/30/20 RULE (simplified):\n- 50% of income → Needs (rent, food, transportation, bills)\n- 30% of income → Wants (entertainment, eating out, hobbies)\n- 20% of income → Savings and investing\n\nIf you are just starting out and do not have many expenses, save even more aggressively.\n\nTHE SAVINGS GOAL LADDER:\n1. Emergency fund: 3-6 months of expenses saved (first goal)\n2. Short-term goals: New phone, car, trip (under 2 years away)\n3. Long-term goals: College, business startup, down payment\n4. Retirement: Start as soon as possible, even if it is small\n\nAUTOMATION IS YOUR FRIEND:\nSet up automatic transfers to savings on payday. Pay yourself first before you have a chance to spend it.\n\nTRACKING YOUR SPENDING:\nFor one month, write down or log every single purchase. You will be shocked at where your money actually goes.\n\nFree budgeting tools: Mint, YNAB (free for students), spreadsheets\n\nREFLECTION:\n- Do you currently have a savings account?\n- What would you cut from your spending to save $50 more per month?\n- What is one financial goal you want to reach in the next 12 months?',
    2, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0004-0003-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000004',
    'Credit, Debt & Traps to Avoid',
    E'CREDIT, DEBT & TRAPS TO AVOID\n\nCredit can be a tool or a trap. The difference is knowledge and discipline.\n\nWHAT IS CREDIT?\nCredit is borrowed money that you promise to repay, usually with interest. Your credit score (300-850) tells lenders how reliably you repay debts.\n\nWhy your credit score matters:\n- Renting an apartment: Landlords check credit\n- Buying a car: Interest rate is based on credit\n- Getting a phone plan: Carriers check credit\n- Employment: Some employers check credit\n\nHOW TO BUILD CREDIT (THE RIGHT WAY):\n1. Become an authorized user on a parent''s card (you build their credit history)\n2. Open a secured credit card (deposit = your credit limit)\n3. Use it for small, regular purchases (gas, groceries)\n4. Pay the FULL balance every month — never carry a balance\n5. Never miss a payment\n\nTHE CREDIT SCORE FACTORS:\n- Payment history (35%): Most important — never miss a payment\n- Utilization (30%): Use less than 30% of your credit limit\n- Length of history (15%): Keep old accounts open\n- Credit mix (10%): Different types of credit help\n- New inquiries (10%): Too many applications hurt you\n\nDEBT TRAPS TO AVOID:\n- Credit card minimum payments: Designed to keep you in debt for years\n- Payday loans: 300-400% APR interest rates are not a typo\n- Buy Now Pay Later apps: Easy to overspend\n- Car payments you cannot afford: A new car loses 20% of its value in year one\n- Lifestyle inflation: Spending more every time you earn more\n\nGOOD DEBT vs. BAD DEBT:\nGood debt creates value over time (student loan for a high-demand career, business loan, mortgage).\nBad debt funds depreciating assets or lifestyle (credit card for clothes, high-interest car loan).\n\nREFLECTION:\n- Do you have any credit history yet?\n- What debt traps do you see people around you falling into?\n- What is your plan to build credit responsibly?',
    3, 20, NOW()
  ),
  (
    '44444444-0004-0004-0000-000000000000',
    '33333333-0000-0000-0000-000000000004',
    'Investing: Making Your Money Work',
    E'INVESTING: MAKING YOUR MONEY WORK\n\nThe earlier you start investing, the more time does the heavy lifting for you. Compound interest is the eighth wonder of the world.\n\nWHAT IS INVESTING?\nInvesting is putting your money to work in assets that grow in value over time. Instead of just saving money that barely keeps pace with inflation, investing grows your wealth.\n\nCOMPOUND INTEREST — THE SUPERPOWER:\nIf you invest $1,000 at age 16 and earn 10% per year on average:\n- At 26: ~$2,594\n- At 36: ~$6,727\n- At 46: ~$17,449\n- At 56: ~$45,259\n\nThe same $1,000 invested at age 36 only becomes ~$6,727 by age 56. Starting earlier is the single most powerful thing you can do.\n\nINVESTMENT BASICS:\n- Stock: A small ownership stake in a company. Stocks grow over time but fluctuate daily.\n- Bond: A loan to a government or company. Lower risk, lower return.\n- Index fund: A basket of many stocks. Diversified and low-cost. Best choice for most beginners.\n- ETF: Similar to an index fund, traded like a stock.\n- Real estate: Property that appreciates and can generate rental income.\n\nWHERE TO START:\n- Roth IRA: A retirement account where your money grows tax-free. Anyone with earned income can open one. Maximum $7,000/year (2024).\n- S&P 500 index fund: Tracks the 500 largest U.S. companies. Historically averages ~10% per year.\n- Custodial brokerage account: A parent can open one for a minor (Fidelity, Schwab, Vanguard)\n\nTHE GOLDEN RULES:\n1. Invest consistently — even small amounts monthly add up\n2. Never invest money you cannot afford to lose short-term\n3. Do not try to time the market — time IN the market beats timing the market\n4. Keep fees low — index funds typically charge 0.03-0.20%\n5. Do not panic sell when markets drop\n\nREFLECTION:\n- Did you know you could open a Roth IRA with your first job income?\n- What is one thing you can cut from your spending to invest monthly?\n- What financial milestone do you want to hit by age 25?',
    4, 20, NOW()
  ),


